28:20.024 --> 28:35.686
experience in coping with different situations, 
especially different situations in Vietnam, to

28:20.024 --> 28:35.686
cope with situations in the States which do not 
ever approach the severity of the situation I was

28:20.024 --> 28:35.686
in. My final question is, Do you feel that serving 
in Vietnam changed you, and if so, how?

28:47.377 --> 28:58.056
I really don't think it changed me in any way that I 
wouldn't have changed ordinarily, except it did

28:47.377 --> 28:58.056
it faster. In other words, if you're going to grow 
up, some people grow up at a certain rate of speed. I

29:05.003 --> 29:06.685
was going at that certain rate of speed. I was doing 
things that you do. I came out of high school and

29:09.449 --> 29:12.172
went to college. I came out of college and went in 
the military. I stayed in the military and things

29:15.036 --> 29:20.102
were just happening for me as they should happen. I 
got married, I had children. I went to Vietnam and

29:24.700 --> 29:29.167
probably matured four for one. I probably came 
back more mature, more aware of people's

29:29.327 --> 29:39.343
problems, more aware that there were more 
problems in the world than taking the trash out to

29:29.327 --> 29:39.343
the curb on a Friday morning. That helped me to grow 
up faster. be more tolerant of other people's

29:42.925 --> 29:52.604
problems and to learn to live with situations that 
are out of the ordinary. Learn to go from a very

29:52.624 --> 30:03.786
comfortable home in the States to a situation in 
Vietnam where suddenly there was, the first time I

29:52.624 --> 30:03.786
saw my uniforms washed on a rock, with a rock 
hitting him on the floor. That, I thought, you

30:07.159 --> 30:12.718
think about how far away that is from a, from a 
washing machine back home. And at the time, It was

30:16.422 --> 30:28.337
very easy to compare, and when I got back from 
Vietnam, it was very easy to look at the things that

30:16.422 --> 30:28.337
we had that we take for granted every day and 
realize how lucky we are and how much we have. And to

30:28.978 --> 30:37.148
also realize that this idealism that we had, that 
we could keep communism out of Vietnam, was really

30:37.837 --> 30:42.064
worthwhile, that we really were fighting for 
something worthwhile. And the way that Saigon is

30:42.865 --> 30:55.024
now Ho Chi Minh City, that the South Vietnamese are 
now under communist rule, tells me that we were

30:42.865 --> 30:55.024
doing the right thing. We were doing it for the 
right cause. I just wish that we could have

30:57.067 --> 31:00.212
accomplished what we set out to do. Thank you very 
much. I appreciate your time.

